WEBVTT

00:02.169 --> 00:05.628
<i>NARRATOR: We lived in an electric world.
We relied on it for everything.</i>

00:06.340 --> 00:08.251
<i>And then the power went out.</i>

00:08.425 --> 00:11.417
<i>Everything stopped working.
We weren't prepared.</i>

00:11.595 --> 00:14.257
<i>Fear and confusion led to panic.</i>

00:14.431 --> 00:16.798
<i>The lucky ones made it out of the cities.</i>

00:16.975 --> 00:19.637
<i>The government collapsed.
Militias took over...</i>

00:19.811 --> 00:22.894
<i>...controlling the food supply
and stockpiling weapons.</i>

00:23.065 --> 00:25.773
<i>We still don't know
why the power went out.</i>

00:25.943 --> 00:29.527
<i>But we're hopeful that someone
will come and light the way.</i>

00:30.280 --> 00:31.896
MAN:
Previously, on Revolution:

00:32.115 --> 00:33.605
I have to ask you to come with us.

00:33.784 --> 00:35.616
DANNY: You can't take him.
- Kid, put it down.

00:35.786 --> 00:37.197
- Stop. Stop.
- Back off.

00:39.248 --> 00:40.784
Danny's gone.

00:40.999 --> 00:43.787
My brother Miles is in Chicago.
He can get Danny.

00:44.002 --> 00:46.334
Why did Monroe want my dad?
Why does he want you?

00:46.547 --> 00:48.163
MILES:
Monroe thinks your dad knew something.

00:48.340 --> 00:50.672
He thinks your dad told me,
so I must know it too.

00:50.884 --> 00:52.420
- What?
- Why the lights went out.

00:52.636 --> 00:54.126
Maybe how to turn them back on.

00:54.304 --> 00:56.511
God knows what they're doing
to Danny now.

00:56.682 --> 00:58.673
You are gonna help me get him back.

00:58.892 --> 01:01.725
- Meet you in two weeks. Lowell, Indiana.
- You're leaving?

01:01.937 --> 01:04.429
- I gotta go get Nora.
- Who is this woman, anyway?

01:04.605 --> 01:07.519
- We can't get Danny back without her.
- Charlie?

01:07.734 --> 01:10.226
"I went after Miles. I'm sorry. Charlie."

01:10.445 --> 01:11.560
MILES:
That's Nora.

01:11.780 --> 01:15.239
I got arrested on purpose.
I'm stealing the sniper rifle.

01:17.327 --> 01:19.034
[GRUNTING]

01:19.204 --> 01:22.413
When did you get that? You're not
selling that sniper rifle, are you?

01:22.624 --> 01:24.911
- You joined the rebels?
- What do you mean, rebels?

01:25.127 --> 01:27.038
They're trying to bring back
the United States.

01:27.212 --> 01:28.794
Ben gave me this.

01:29.006 --> 01:31.873
We take this to this Grace woman,
and she does what with it?

01:32.092 --> 01:34.834
AARON: Ben just said she knew something
about the power.

01:52.112 --> 01:53.694
MILES:
Nora, come on, be reasonable.

01:53.905 --> 01:57.739
- We've been over this, Miles.
- It's just a gun like that?

01:58.493 --> 02:01.656
Hard to find these days.
You should keep it.

02:01.872 --> 02:03.408
Use it to get her brother back.

02:03.624 --> 02:06.036
The rebels need it.
More than we do.

02:06.585 --> 02:09.418
You're really serious about this, huh?
Full-on rebel now.

02:09.630 --> 02:12.543
- Why is that so hard to understand?
MILES: Because I know you.

02:12.758 --> 02:15.170
It's not like you to fight for a lost cause.

02:16.637 --> 02:18.628
I fought for us, didn't I?

02:19.640 --> 02:22.257
Uh, is this a private conversation?

02:22.476 --> 02:24.058
- No.
- Yes.

02:24.895 --> 02:26.431
I'm just...

02:26.855 --> 02:28.311
...trying to look out for you.

02:30.901 --> 02:34.439
You think you and your rebel pals
are gonna bring back the United States?

02:34.655 --> 02:35.895
Really?

02:36.531 --> 02:38.317
They're gonna butcher you.

02:38.533 --> 02:42.071
I wonder.
If you really believe all that...

02:42.287 --> 02:45.575
...or if you're just scared of going up
against Monroe.

02:47.542 --> 02:49.829
<i>MONROE: You've gone insane, Miles,
you know that, right?</i>

02:50.712 --> 02:53.670
MILES: Rest of the world's gone insane.
I'm just keeping up.

02:53.882 --> 02:57.591
Okay. Right. Well, one,
you're going AWOL.

02:57.761 --> 02:59.502
And two...

02:59.805 --> 03:01.671
What, are you gonna
walk to Chicago?

03:02.057 --> 03:05.049
- I gotta find my brother.
- It's like a thousand miles away.

03:05.268 --> 03:07.009
I'm not gonna just sit here.

03:08.146 --> 03:12.105
Everybody's just sitting here.
Waiting for orders that aren't gonna come.

03:17.656 --> 03:19.192
Okay.

03:20.158 --> 03:21.865
All right, let me pack.

03:22.744 --> 03:23.779
What?

03:24.830 --> 03:25.911
I'm coming with you.

03:26.081 --> 03:29.995
No, Bass, you're not.
I'm not dragging you into this.

03:30.293 --> 03:33.911
My family. My problem.

03:34.715 --> 03:38.549
And you're my family.
That makes it my problem.

03:41.471 --> 03:43.337
I'm not asking you.

03:58.196 --> 04:00.278
This is your rebel base?

04:10.250 --> 04:11.365
MAN 1 :
Hey.

04:13.170 --> 04:14.331
MAN 2:
Don't move.

04:16.798 --> 04:18.505
Take it easy.

04:19.176 --> 04:20.791
NICHOLAS:
It's okay.

04:22.679 --> 04:25.467
- Nora. Thank God.
- Nicholas.

04:25.640 --> 04:26.926
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

04:35.192 --> 04:36.728
You got the rifle, heh.

04:37.569 --> 04:39.185
Did you ever doubt it?

04:41.072 --> 04:42.153
<i>H9'! -</i>

04:43.158 --> 04:45.024
I'm Stu Red man .

04:45.452 --> 04:47.159
This is Frannie.

04:48.955 --> 04:50.161
They're friends of mine.

04:51.416 --> 04:54.499
Listen. We're in trouble. It's bad.

04:55.045 --> 04:56.456
What do you mean?

04:58.131 --> 04:59.713
[PEOPLE COUGHING]

05:03.762 --> 05:05.503
Oh, my God.

05:09.017 --> 05:10.599
What the hell happened?

05:16.233 --> 05:17.849
NORA:
Easy. Easy.

05:22.447 --> 05:24.905
WOMAN:
Hey, you. A little help.

05:26.535 --> 05:28.822
Keep pressure right here.

05:37.796 --> 05:40.083
IcanT,I can%""

05:42.425 --> 05:44.462
We went on a raid this morning.

05:44.678 --> 05:46.635
Militia supply dump out in Chatsworth.

05:46.805 --> 05:48.842
We were trying
to score some guns, but...

05:49.057 --> 05:52.175
...it was a trap.
Soldiers came from everywhere.

05:52.394 --> 05:54.726
Are all your people accounted for?

05:55.355 --> 05:56.390
Twelve dead.

05:58.275 --> 06:00.858
- One missing.
- Missing? Was he captured?

06:01.069 --> 06:03.310
- I don't know.
- You don't know.

06:03.530 --> 06:06.739
What if he was?
What if he's giving up your position?

06:06.950 --> 06:08.156
And who are you?

06:11.872 --> 06:13.738
NORA:
Nick. We can't stay here.

06:13.957 --> 06:16.790
- We gotta patch these people up and go.
- We're in no shape to travel.

06:17.002 --> 06:18.413
You don't have a choice, pal.

06:18.628 --> 06:21.666
- Militia could be coming right now.
CHARLIE: Guys.

06:26.344 --> 06:28.426
That man's dead.

06:32.726 --> 06:35.969
This is what being a rebel gets you.

06:43.862 --> 06:45.523
Just tell me.

06:47.198 --> 06:49.530
Where's your rebel camp?

06:49.951 --> 06:51.942
[WHIMPERING]

06:53.038 --> 06:54.699
Okay.

06:55.874 --> 06:57.205
[GUN CLICKS]

07:02.005 --> 07:05.043
You know how hard it is
to find a bullet these days?

07:06.217 --> 07:07.833
I mean a proper bullet.

07:08.053 --> 07:11.466
Smokeless powder.
Copper jacket.

07:11.973 --> 07:13.680
That kind of thing.

07:14.351 --> 07:16.388
You know, they can't even make them.

07:16.853 --> 07:20.312
Not in this medieval cesspool.

07:21.358 --> 07:26.603
Nope, we've gotta go
scavenging for antiques.

07:29.574 --> 07:31.235
Where's your rebel camp?

07:33.286 --> 07:34.572
[GUN CLICKS]

07:35.705 --> 07:37.696
[HOSTAGE WHIMPERING AND COUGHING]

07:38.083 --> 07:43.795
Yes, siree, bullets are about as rare
and precious as diamonds.

07:44.589 --> 07:47.923
Which is why I only put
one bullet in this gun.

07:48.134 --> 07:50.842
And why I would prefer not to use it.

07:51.972 --> 07:53.007
[GUN CLICKING]

07:53.181 --> 07:56.799
We're gonna get there sooner or later
until you tell me where your camp is.

07:56.977 --> 07:58.968
[STAMMERING]

07:59.854 --> 08:02.061
Five miles east down the road.

08:02.273 --> 08:03.763
The old restaurant.

08:04.526 --> 08:06.233
Thank you.

08:06.444 --> 08:08.060
Appreciate that.

08:11.074 --> 08:12.109
Get ready to move out.

08:14.035 --> 08:16.618
And tell the men, no survivors.

08:35.181 --> 08:37.172
[HORSE NEIGHS]

08:54.868 --> 08:55.903
Here.

08:58.621 --> 09:00.282
Ah, damn, I'm sorry.

09:01.833 --> 09:04.996
- You got a problem?
- What? No.

09:05.170 --> 09:07.286
What possible problem could I--?
Oh, wait.

09:07.797 --> 09:10.835
You know, there was that one time
in your little crap village...

09:11.009 --> 09:13.216
...where you shot my best friend
with a crossbow.

09:14.137 --> 09:16.720
So, yeah, I guess there's that.

09:18.099 --> 09:21.012
Your best friend murdered my father.

09:21.186 --> 09:25.931
Which, uh, let's be honest,
was probably no big loss, right?

09:30.445 --> 09:32.402
Captain Neville.

09:33.198 --> 09:34.404
What?

09:35.492 --> 09:38.280
If you want me dead, just kill me.

09:38.453 --> 09:40.035
Otherwise...

09:41.247 --> 09:43.739
...I'd like some water, please.

09:46.711 --> 09:49.078
You heard the boy.
Give him some water.

09:51.925 --> 09:53.882
Yes, sir.

10:05.271 --> 10:07.854
I don't wanna break up your little, uh...

10:08.191 --> 10:11.559
Whatever this is. We need to talk.

10:17.992 --> 10:19.903
Take your hands off me.

10:20.078 --> 10:21.660
We did it, okay?

10:21.871 --> 10:24.829
We delivered your stupid rifle
to your whiny-ass rebel buddies.

10:24.999 --> 10:26.910
- It's time to go.
- Look around you.

10:27.085 --> 10:28.325
These people are hurt.

10:28.503 --> 10:31.416
You don't get it.
What happened, that was a kill order.

10:31.714 --> 10:34.376
Militia's gonna be hunting for them.
It is not safe.

10:34.551 --> 10:36.417
All the more reason to get them out.

10:36.594 --> 10:39.632
- We're looking for her brother.
- Exactly.

10:39.806 --> 10:41.717
It's my brother, so this is my call.

10:42.559 --> 10:44.049
Excuse me?

10:44.894 --> 10:48.307
- How much time do you need?
- Half hour, tops.

10:48.481 --> 10:51.269
- That's a promise?
- Oh, you are joking.

10:51.442 --> 10:54.855
All you ever say is, "We gotta
find Danny, we need to find Danny."

10:55.029 --> 10:58.021
That clock's ticking. Now, you wanna
hang around, play wet nurse?

10:58.199 --> 11:00.531
You said we needed her
to get Danny back.

11:00.702 --> 11:03.034
Needed. Those were your exact words.

11:05.165 --> 11:06.951
Right?

11:07.167 --> 11:10.205
So she's staying, I'm staying.

11:10.587 --> 11:12.624
And you can do whatever you want.

11:35.320 --> 11:38.529
So the woman who can turn
the power back on lives...

11:38.698 --> 11:40.109
...here.

11:42.660 --> 11:46.028
It's a little low-key, I'll give you that.

11:59.802 --> 12:01.292
Hello.

12:01.888 --> 12:03.845
Grace Beaumont?

12:10.396 --> 12:11.727
Stop.

12:13.983 --> 12:15.974
Something's wrong.

12:26.287 --> 12:27.994
Grace?

13:10.290 --> 13:11.951
This is...

13:12.125 --> 13:13.581
[CHUCKLES]

13:13.751 --> 13:15.788
It's an eight-bit register.

13:17.046 --> 13:18.411
An ID connector.

13:20.258 --> 13:22.124
A CPU.

13:22.302 --> 13:26.717
Last time I saw one of these,
I was happy and so, so rich.

13:26.889 --> 13:30.098
If I didn't know any better,
and I am not sure that I do...

13:30.268 --> 13:33.181
...I would say that Grace Beaumont
built herself a computer.

13:34.314 --> 13:36.931
- That's--
-insane. Cuckoo for Cocoa Puffs.

13:37.108 --> 13:40.351
Who would build a computer
unless they had electricity?

13:40.570 --> 13:43.983
Aaron, we can't stay.
Something bad happened here...

13:44.157 --> 13:46.945
...happened to Grace.
What if whoever did it comes back?

13:48.870 --> 13:52.363
We risk it.
I gotta figure out what's going on here.

13:52.915 --> 13:59.287
Because if Grace really had power,
and it sort of looks like she did...

13:59.672 --> 14:03.131
...how is anything more important?

14:08.973 --> 14:10.463
CHARLIE:
You'll be okay.

14:11.267 --> 14:13.178
I broke this one in three places.

14:13.353 --> 14:15.890
- Healed just fine.
- How'd you do it?

14:16.105 --> 14:20.440
A boy from my village, he was a bully.

14:20.610 --> 14:22.726
A real dick, actually, heh.

14:22.904 --> 14:27.489
He's about five years older
and 5O pounds bigger than me.

14:27.658 --> 14:30.195
But I still managed
to knock his front teeth out.

14:31.037 --> 14:34.701
- Remind me not to pick a fight with you.
- I will.

14:36.167 --> 14:38.283
Okay, I think I get it now.

14:40.213 --> 14:41.328
Get what?

14:42.048 --> 14:45.416
It's, uh, Shaq over there, isn't it?

14:47.387 --> 14:49.628
The honest love of a good man.

14:49.847 --> 14:52.464
It's why you're fighting
with these amateurs?

14:52.642 --> 14:53.973
Wow.

14:54.143 --> 14:56.635
Can you boil everything down
to getting laid?

14:57.647 --> 14:58.853
Yeah.

14:59.982 --> 15:02.565
You're acting like a jealous kid.

15:02.777 --> 15:05.815
Well, something happened to you.

15:06.030 --> 15:09.022
- I'm betting it's that guy.
- He's a priest.

15:09.575 --> 15:10.656
Sorry?

15:10.827 --> 15:13.194
Nicholas. He's a Catholic priest.

15:14.497 --> 15:17.535
Oh, so you're not his type.

15:20.378 --> 15:24.212
- Hey, look, I'm just trying to understand.
- You're right, okay? I'm here for a guy.

15:24.382 --> 15:27.170
And it's not Nicholas. And drop it.

15:29.679 --> 15:32.296
Five minutes. Then we're gone.

15:35.935 --> 15:38.267
Put as much distance
between you and here as possible.

15:38.729 --> 15:42.768
We don't know each other,
we don't talk to each other. Low profile.

15:42.942 --> 15:45.400
Two months from today, we'll
rendezvous at Bloomington Base.

15:45.570 --> 15:46.605
[GUNSHOTS]

15:46.779 --> 15:48.065
CHARLIE:
Get down!

15:48.239 --> 15:49.775
[WOMAN GROANS]

15:49.949 --> 15:51.030
Fire!

15:54.579 --> 15:56.616
SOLDIER 1:
Prepare to fire!

15:57.707 --> 15:59.118
SOLDIER 2: Ready!
- Fire!

16:04.547 --> 16:05.708
Fire!

16:07.592 --> 16:08.707
[PANTING]

16:17.560 --> 16:18.675
Fire!

16:20.813 --> 16:23.396
May Christ admit you
into his heavenly kingdom.

16:23.566 --> 16:25.853
And enjoy the vision of God for...

16:32.742 --> 16:34.483
- Who's your best shot?
- Trevor.

16:34.660 --> 16:36.571
[GUNSHOTS AND GLASS SHATTERING]

16:37.371 --> 16:39.988
Get up to the roof.
Anyone comes within 1 O yards, fire.

16:40.166 --> 16:43.625
Hurry, before they ram the doors in.
Just buy us some time.

16:43.794 --> 16:45.410
[GUNSHOTS]

16:45.755 --> 16:47.166
Padre.

16:49.634 --> 16:51.750
NORA:
Charlie. Charlie.

16:52.678 --> 16:53.713
[SIGHS]

16:53.888 --> 16:55.674
Sam was a sweet kid.

16:55.848 --> 16:58.681
But you can't lose it, not now.

16:58.851 --> 17:00.012
Now I need your help.

17:01.771 --> 17:03.603
[GUNSHOTS AND GLASS SHATTERING]

17:04.022 --> 17:07.686
SOLDIER 1: Advance!
SOLDIER 2: On the door.

17:22.458 --> 17:23.914
SOLDIER 3: Someone on the roof!
SOLDIER 4: Shooter!

17:25.002 --> 17:26.788
[GUNSHOTS]

17:28.130 --> 17:31.668
- Fall back!
SOLDIER 5: Fall back, fall back!

17:36.347 --> 17:37.883
NICHOLAS:
What the hell are you doing?

17:38.057 --> 17:41.266
We don't have the proper equipment,
shovels or anything.

17:42.478 --> 17:46.346
So we'll break the legs off chairs,
use kitchen tools, whatever we got.

17:46.566 --> 17:48.477
Chair legs? To dig a tunnel?

17:48.651 --> 17:50.517
There's a lot of men out there, okay?

17:50.695 --> 17:52.606
Sooner or later, they're coming in...

17:52.780 --> 17:55.021
...so we are gonna
Shawshank our asses out of here.

17:55.199 --> 17:56.234
[SCOFFS]

17:56.409 --> 17:57.524
Come on.

17:59.954 --> 18:01.240
Go.

18:02.331 --> 18:03.662
[GUNSHOT]

18:08.170 --> 18:09.660
Sir, your orders?

18:11.465 --> 18:14.082
- Send in another man.
- Sir, he's cutting us down.

18:14.677 --> 18:17.669
And do you know what
he is cutting us down with, sergeant?

18:19.056 --> 18:20.842
A Marine Corps M40A.

18:21.017 --> 18:26.262
And that is the reason it is illegal
for citizens to own firearms.

18:26.731 --> 18:28.438
Squeezing off five rounds...

18:28.608 --> 18:31.350
...in the amount of time
it takes us to load one.

18:31.527 --> 18:34.770
Seems to have, heh,
a remarkable amount of ammo.

18:34.947 --> 18:38.065
But you and I know that bullets are rare.

18:38.284 --> 18:41.197
Which means sooner or later,
he is going to run out.

18:41.370 --> 18:44.362
So let's just try to help him along
a little, shall we?

18:45.791 --> 18:47.873
Send in another man.

18:49.629 --> 18:51.961
Send in another man.

18:54.467 --> 18:55.582
Yes, sir.

18:56.844 --> 18:57.925
[GUNSHOT]

18:58.095 --> 18:59.176
[SOLDIER GRUNTS]

19:00.848 --> 19:02.430
Terrific.

19:09.940 --> 19:12.398
Anyone trips that,
the bleach hits the potassium chloride...

19:12.568 --> 19:15.606
...and they'll end up with theirjunk
in their hands. Literally.

19:21.744 --> 19:23.906
Nora, you think
you'll be able to beat Monroe?

19:24.372 --> 19:26.454
I don't think
we're getting out of here alive.

19:26.624 --> 19:28.615
You know what I mean. If you do.

19:29.293 --> 19:32.001
Probably not. We're too outmanned.

19:33.130 --> 19:35.041
But then, why are you here?

19:40.888 --> 19:43.175
Yeah, I was with your uncle for a while.

19:43.349 --> 19:46.683
But after that, there was Frank.
He was sweet.

19:46.852 --> 19:50.390
Had no idea who I was,
what I could do.

19:53.192 --> 19:55.024
One night though,
we went for a walk...

19:55.194 --> 19:57.481
...and these drunk militia dicks
stopped us.

19:57.655 --> 19:58.736
They were getting cute.

19:59.156 --> 20:01.022
Frank thought he had to be macho...

20:01.242 --> 20:03.358
...defend my honor or whatever.

20:03.577 --> 20:05.488
They were beating him up pretty bad.

20:05.663 --> 20:08.030
So I knocked them out cold.

20:08.249 --> 20:09.990
I took a few hard shots, but...

20:11.335 --> 20:12.700
What happened to Frank?

20:12.878 --> 20:14.243
[GUNSHOT IN DISTANCE]

20:16.173 --> 20:17.629
He dumped me.

20:17.800 --> 20:20.588
I think he was a little bit scared of me.

20:22.221 --> 20:23.256
I don't understand.

20:23.431 --> 20:26.765
You told Miles
that you joined the rebels over a guy.

20:29.437 --> 20:32.975
Yeah. But it wasn't Frank.

20:34.442 --> 20:38.561
It wasn't even a guy
so much as it was...

20:39.488 --> 20:41.320
...a little boy.

20:43.868 --> 20:46.235
I was five months pregnant that night.

20:49.999 --> 20:54.334
But the next morning, I wasn't.

20:57.631 --> 20:59.713
Oh, God, Nora, I'm so sorry.

21:00.843 --> 21:02.925
That's why I'm here, Charlie.

21:03.095 --> 21:04.335
Win or lose.

21:04.513 --> 21:07.505
Because I had to make it
mean something.

21:08.476 --> 21:11.389
And if I have another baby...

21:12.021 --> 21:14.683
...it'll be born in the United States.

21:34.877 --> 21:37.414
Up and at them, sunshine.

21:40.299 --> 21:44.463
You looking for Captain Neville?
Sorry, he went into town.

21:45.679 --> 21:47.545
It's just you and me.

21:48.098 --> 21:50.180
Now, where were we?

21:51.811 --> 21:53.597
Oh, yeah.

21:54.104 --> 21:55.970
You killed my friend.

21:56.690 --> 21:58.931
Now, look, he, uh--

21:59.109 --> 22:01.100
- Templeton.
- Okay.

22:01.278 --> 22:04.191
- Okay, Templeton--
- Show him some respect.

22:04.365 --> 22:07.528
His name was Templeton.

22:07.868 --> 22:11.202
He had a wife. Carol.

22:11.372 --> 22:14.330
Huge girl, heh, heh, heh...

22:14.875 --> 22:16.081
...but he loved her.

22:17.586 --> 22:21.955
So now I gotta go tell Big Carol
what happened.

22:22.132 --> 22:26.922
And she's gonna look me in the eye
and she's gonna say:

22:27.096 --> 22:29.463
"But you got payback, right?"

22:31.892 --> 22:34.224
And you know what
I'm gonna tell her?

22:35.521 --> 22:37.353
"Yes, I did.

22:38.440 --> 22:41.683
Again and again."

22:42.653 --> 22:44.564
- Just hold on.
- And again.

22:44.738 --> 22:47.105
Captain Neville, he wants me alive.

22:47.449 --> 22:50.532
Oh, you'll be alive. Don't worry.

22:50.703 --> 22:52.114
You'll just wish you weren't.

22:53.122 --> 22:55.113
[GRUNTING]

23:35.497 --> 23:38.910
Miles, we can't do anything,
let's just keep walking, okay?

23:39.501 --> 23:41.959
How many bodies have we come across?

23:42.504 --> 23:44.211
Just like this.

23:47.676 --> 23:50.589
I don't understand how things
can fall apart so fast.

23:50.804 --> 23:52.920
Well, what do you expect, man?

23:53.140 --> 23:55.677
People are hungry.

23:56.352 --> 23:59.845
- Hungry people get desperate.
- Yeah. But this?

24:02.942 --> 24:04.774
Ain't nobody coming to help.

24:09.114 --> 24:10.604
No one.

24:17.289 --> 24:18.779
[GUNSHOT]

24:20.542 --> 24:22.874
MILES: How many rounds
do you think he's got left?

24:24.380 --> 24:26.291
We'll get out of here.

24:27.216 --> 24:32.302
Well, must be nice to have faith.
Must make you feel real confident.

24:40.062 --> 24:41.097
[GUNSHOT]

24:44.358 --> 24:47.146
Unh. Son of a bitch.

24:56.245 --> 24:57.827
All wired up.

24:58.414 --> 25:00.246
[WOOD CREAKING]

25:00.416 --> 25:02.077
[GRUNTING]

25:03.502 --> 25:04.663
NORA:
Albert.

25:07.297 --> 25:08.708
NICHOLAS:
You got him?

25:09.591 --> 25:10.706
Do you got him?

25:10.884 --> 25:12.340
[GRUNTING]

25:15.097 --> 25:16.838
[MILES PANTING]

25:17.016 --> 25:18.723
NICHOLAS:
You okay?

25:20.436 --> 25:21.926
So, what now?

25:22.312 --> 25:23.643
[GUNSHOT]

25:24.189 --> 25:26.351
I don't know. Dig it out again, I guess.

25:26.525 --> 25:27.890
[GUNSHOTS]

25:28.068 --> 25:29.229
[MAN SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY]

25:29.403 --> 25:30.518
And we're out of ammo.

25:31.030 --> 25:33.567
This is crazy. We don't have time
to dig another tunnel.

25:33.782 --> 25:36.114
- What's your brilliant idea?
- We fight them off.

25:36.285 --> 25:38.902
There's 50 men up there.
You cannot stop them.

25:39.079 --> 25:40.444
That's what my dad used to say.

25:40.622 --> 25:42.613
Every time
the soldiers came to our town...

25:42.791 --> 25:44.782
...and they'd take our crops
and our women.

25:44.960 --> 25:48.078
- I bet he said it when they came for him.
- He was trying to protect you.

25:48.255 --> 25:49.916
He was being a coward.

25:51.050 --> 25:55.135
Don't ever, ever disrespect your dad.

25:59.266 --> 26:01.132
Are we clear?

26:03.812 --> 26:05.803
[EXPLOSION]

26:07.274 --> 26:10.266
- Trip wire. They're coming in.
- We still got men up there.

26:10.486 --> 26:14.400
Charlie, wait here. I mean it.

26:19.161 --> 26:20.276
[MAN YELLS]

26:21.163 --> 26:22.494
[GUNSHOT]

26:23.791 --> 26:25.498
[GRUNTING]

26:26.752 --> 26:28.083
[GUNSHOT]

26:32.674 --> 26:34.335
[GRUNTING]

26:45.771 --> 26:46.806
Miles.

26:48.023 --> 26:49.889
[BOTH GRUNTING]

26:54.113 --> 26:56.195
Stay back. Or he's dead.

26:57.950 --> 27:00.191
NORA: Move, move, move.
MAN: Hurry up, man.

27:00.452 --> 27:02.193
MILES:
Lock the door.

27:02.412 --> 27:04.028
Nora, rope.

27:07.960 --> 27:09.121
What's this about?

27:10.045 --> 27:11.786
He's their C.O.

27:13.006 --> 27:15.464
We can trade him, his life for ours.

27:15.676 --> 27:19.214
Miles. It really is you, isn't it?

27:20.347 --> 27:22.008
Who's Miles?

27:22.975 --> 27:24.010
You know this guy?

27:27.437 --> 27:29.394
Oh, you really don't know, do you?

27:30.315 --> 27:31.851
How do you know him?

27:34.653 --> 27:37.520
Well, they're gonna find out
sooner or later.

27:37.739 --> 27:40.731
Go ahead. Tell them.

27:43.078 --> 27:45.740
This is Miles Matheson.

27:46.081 --> 27:49.540
Commanding general
of the Monroe Militia.

27:49.710 --> 27:51.701
A damn founding father
of the republic...

27:51.879 --> 27:55.713
...second only
to Sebastian Monroe himself.

28:02.764 --> 28:05.256
He taught me everything I know.

28:07.269 --> 28:08.600
Miles?

28:22.993 --> 28:25.405
- I ought to slit your throat.
- Padre.

28:25.579 --> 28:28.913
- Thought you were all about forgiveness.
- Christ forgives. I'm not Christ.

28:30.167 --> 28:33.910
- You knew this whole time.
NICHOLAS: Wait a minute.

28:34.379 --> 28:37.542
You brought Miles Matheson in here
on purpose?

28:37.716 --> 28:39.582
This is so dramatic.

28:39.760 --> 28:42.548
- Do you remember One <i>Life</i> to <i>Live?</i>
- Shut up.

28:42.763 --> 28:46.256
Look. Be pissed, hate me,
do what you gotta do.

28:46.433 --> 28:49.721
But we got bigger fish, okay?
We trade him, we get out of here.

28:49.895 --> 28:52.683
- Won't matter.
- Yes, it will.

28:53.106 --> 28:56.895
Because like he said, I made the rules.

28:57.778 --> 29:00.816
Well, the rules of engagement
have changed, kitten.

29:00.989 --> 29:03.777
Monroe's done negotiating with traitors.

29:03.992 --> 29:05.903
- You're a bad liar.
JEREMY: I'm a bad liar?

29:06.119 --> 29:08.577
Look me in the eye
and tell me I'm a liar.

29:12.459 --> 29:14.666
So let me go, don't.

29:14.836 --> 29:16.292
I've made peace with my Lord.

29:16.463 --> 29:19.330
When my men come in here and cut you up,
you'll have to make peace--

29:19.508 --> 29:20.919
[GRUNTS]

29:26.723 --> 29:29.090
I just-- I'm confused.

29:31.019 --> 29:33.932
So General Monroe, you know him?

29:34.106 --> 29:35.938
I am not talking about this right now.

29:36.108 --> 29:40.067
- Well, I think I deserve an explanation.
- Really? Do you?

29:40.654 --> 29:43.362
Okay. Yeah.

29:43.782 --> 29:46.774
I know him. Very well.

29:47.327 --> 29:49.694
You were in charge of the whole militia?

29:49.913 --> 29:52.280
Been a few years, but, yep.

29:54.126 --> 29:56.709
You murdered people's fathers,
dragged away their brothers.

29:56.878 --> 29:59.836
Yes, Charlie. I killed fathers and sons
and husbands and--

30:00.007 --> 30:01.964
Is that what you wanna know?
You happy?

30:04.469 --> 30:07.211
Do not talk to me that way.

30:07.389 --> 30:10.723
I am just trying to understand
what's going on.

30:10.934 --> 30:12.424
Well...

30:12.602 --> 30:14.138
...now you know.

30:16.481 --> 30:19.769
Now you know why the militia
cannot be stopped...

30:19.943 --> 30:21.980
...because they're mine.

30:24.948 --> 30:26.530
I trained them.

30:27.284 --> 30:32.120
And they are brutal
and smart and vicious...

30:32.289 --> 30:34.246
...because of me.

30:35.250 --> 30:36.991
That's why your dad was right.

30:37.711 --> 30:41.921
When you see them coming,
you don't fight. You run.

30:49.514 --> 30:52.973
MAGGIE: Any progress?
- No.

30:53.435 --> 30:56.928
Pretty much a sucking black hole
of nothing.

30:58.482 --> 31:01.395
I found some supplies.
Salt, curry.

31:03.487 --> 31:07.196
That's great. Oh, that's great.
Oh, and curry...?

31:07.366 --> 31:08.777
Great.

31:10.577 --> 31:12.488
- You're frustrated.
- Frustrated?

31:13.872 --> 31:16.489
"Frustrated" doesn't even scratch it.

31:16.666 --> 31:18.657
What is all of this crap?

31:18.835 --> 31:21.998
And what is this ugly-ass thing
even for?

31:22.964 --> 31:25.956
- Why did Ben even give it to me?
- Aaron.

31:26.134 --> 31:31.595
It's like Lucy yanking some enormous,
cosmic football...

31:31.765 --> 31:33.972
...just as Charlie Brown's
about to kick it.

31:38.522 --> 31:40.138
I'll be downstairs.

31:49.282 --> 31:51.193
SOLDIER 1: Ready!
SOLDIER 2: Watch it.

31:51.368 --> 31:52.403
[THUDDING]

31:52.577 --> 31:53.612
SOLDIER 3:
Again!

31:54.454 --> 31:55.615
SOLDIER 4:
Try something else!

31:56.456 --> 31:58.493
NICHOLAS:
Look, Nora. We just don't have a choice.

31:58.708 --> 32:00.244
- That's your plan?
NICHOLAS: Listen.

32:00.419 --> 32:02.786
We charge out that door,
half of us won't make it.

32:02.963 --> 32:04.453
Half is better than none.

32:04.631 --> 32:08.295
- Now, if you have a better idea--
- It's easy to have a better idea...

32:08.468 --> 32:10.084
...because that idea is awful.

32:10.262 --> 32:13.596
- I'd keep my mouth shut if I were you.
- Take it easy, your holiness.

32:13.765 --> 32:17.008
- I'm about to save your sorry asses.
- Miles, how?

32:17.477 --> 32:19.138
We make a trade.

32:23.650 --> 32:25.357
So...

32:27.320 --> 32:29.857
You let these people go,
I'll turn myself in.

32:30.073 --> 32:32.405
- What?
- To you.

32:32.576 --> 32:33.657
Miles, no.

32:34.161 --> 32:39.577
That's a good deal, right?
I bet you'd get a parade for this.

32:40.041 --> 32:41.327
Hmm.

32:41.501 --> 32:43.117
I want that rifle.

32:43.503 --> 32:45.494
The one you were taking potshots
at us with.

32:46.047 --> 32:47.287
Done.

32:47.466 --> 32:49.628
What makes you think
he'll keep his side?

32:49.843 --> 32:52.710
I've known this guy for much longer
than I've known any of you.

32:53.180 --> 32:54.511
He'll keep his word.

32:54.723 --> 32:57.055
Yeah, and what about your word?

32:57.934 --> 33:00.016
Can't find Danny if you're dead.

33:03.106 --> 33:04.517
All right.

33:06.651 --> 33:08.312
Let's go.

33:13.992 --> 33:15.903
[MEN SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY]

33:20.457 --> 33:21.788
They're gonna kill him.

33:23.502 --> 33:25.163
He's a war criminal.

33:26.338 --> 33:28.045
And aren't you a priest?

33:28.840 --> 33:30.376
Doesn't change what he's done.

33:32.010 --> 33:36.345
Sorry. I can only pray that the Lord
will have mercy on his soul.

33:39.601 --> 33:41.592
[COUGHING]

33:43.438 --> 33:44.928
Hey, man.

33:45.148 --> 33:47.856
So just you and me.
What do you want to do?

33:48.068 --> 33:51.060
- Leave me alone.
- You're not still upset about before?

33:51.821 --> 33:54.313
- I don't want any...
- What? I can't hear you.

33:54.533 --> 33:57.400
- No, no, no.
- Look, stop screwing around.

33:58.370 --> 34:00.862
I have asthma, I have asthma. I need...

34:01.039 --> 34:02.450
[DANNY WHEEZING AND COUGHING]

34:02.624 --> 34:04.740
Hey, hey, hey. Quit it. Hey, hey.

34:04.918 --> 34:06.283
Hey, Captain Neville--?

34:06.461 --> 34:08.077
[GRUNTING]

34:09.839 --> 34:13.706
You touch me again, and I'll kill you.

34:13.885 --> 34:16.297
I'll kill you! You understand me?

34:16.471 --> 34:17.552
[GASPING]

34:17.722 --> 34:18.962
Do you?

34:22.476 --> 34:24.138
[COUGHING]

34:36.408 --> 34:40.197
JEREMY:
Miles. It's me. You can level with me.

34:41.413 --> 34:43.154
Is it true?

34:43.331 --> 34:45.447
Is what true?

34:45.625 --> 34:47.331
Well, the rumor is...

34:47.502 --> 34:51.335
...Monroe wants you because you know
something about flipping the lights on.

34:52.674 --> 34:54.335
It's crazy, right?

34:55.467 --> 34:58.677
- What do you think?
- Oh, I think it's crazy.

34:59.139 --> 35:02.882
I think Monroe's obsessed.

35:03.643 --> 35:05.384
It's sort of worrisome.

35:06.229 --> 35:08.061
I'll tell you something else.

35:08.231 --> 35:11.064
He hasn't been the same since you left.

35:11.234 --> 35:13.316
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

35:13.486 --> 35:16.228
He's angrier.

35:16.406 --> 35:18.272
Shorter fuse, you know?

35:20.577 --> 35:22.989
Not like the good old days.

35:30.629 --> 35:31.915
[NEIGHING]

35:32.088 --> 35:34.079
[SOLDIERS SCREAMING AND GRUNTING]

35:41.264 --> 35:42.675
[GRUNTING]

35:44.601 --> 35:46.091
Come on.

36:49.416 --> 36:50.906
[MAN GRUNTING]

36:58.299 --> 37:01.041
Miles, no. Come on, man,
let's just keep walking.

37:01.261 --> 37:03.002
You don't have to come.

37:09.561 --> 37:11.427
MILES:
Get away from him.

37:16.568 --> 37:19.185
This ain't none of your business.

37:22.282 --> 37:25.991
- I said get away from him.
- Whoa, whoa, hey. Take it easy.

37:29.581 --> 37:30.867
Here.

37:33.376 --> 37:34.958
Look.

37:35.420 --> 37:38.629
- I would just get the hell out of here.
- No.

37:41.593 --> 37:42.924
Do not move.

37:47.640 --> 37:48.880
Miles?

37:49.350 --> 37:51.057
Look, man, I'm sorry.

37:51.227 --> 37:53.639
We're just trying to find
something to eat.

37:54.439 --> 37:56.897
That couple back up the road.

37:57.525 --> 37:58.981
In the orange tent.

38:05.658 --> 38:09.242
Yeah, that was you. Thought so.

38:14.793 --> 38:16.909
We can't call the cops.

38:20.340 --> 38:22.832
- Can't put them in jail.
MONROE: Miles, Miles.

38:23.218 --> 38:24.879
This is over.

38:28.973 --> 38:30.008
[GUNSHOT]

38:39.275 --> 38:41.186
What did you just do?

38:43.279 --> 38:46.067
There's nobody else coming to help.
It's just us out here.

38:46.241 --> 38:48.027
So you're gonna walk around
wasting guys--

38:48.201 --> 38:50.818
Somebody's gotta do something.

38:54.833 --> 38:56.915
Or else there's gonna be nothing left.

39:00.839 --> 39:02.250
<i>H9'! -</i>

39:02.423 --> 39:04.164
Mister, you all right?

39:06.177 --> 39:07.212
Thank you.

39:09.347 --> 39:11.679
You saved my life.

39:11.850 --> 39:13.932
[JEREMY GROANING]

39:32.745 --> 39:34.201
All right, let's hear it.

39:34.372 --> 39:35.828
Hear what?

39:36.708 --> 39:38.824
Tell me I'm a monster.

39:39.002 --> 39:40.913
That I'm garbage.

39:41.337 --> 39:44.875
Miles Matheson, general of the militia.

39:45.383 --> 39:48.216
- Come on, I wanna hear you say it.
- I'm not gonna say it.

39:48.386 --> 39:50.468
MILES: Why not?
- Because I don't think it.

39:50.680 --> 39:52.091
Yes, you do.

39:52.515 --> 39:54.176
How can you not?

39:55.226 --> 39:58.435
- You don't understand, Charlie.
- So tell me. I wanna understand.

39:58.605 --> 40:01.188
No, you really don't.

40:01.357 --> 40:04.395
Well, fact is, you still saved
all those people back there.

40:05.111 --> 40:08.570
So obviously there's a part of you
that still gives a crap.

40:13.453 --> 40:14.943
You're wrong.

40:20.877 --> 40:22.333
AARON:
You wanna hear a joke?

40:23.046 --> 40:25.708
- Sorry?
- You'll love it.

40:25.924 --> 40:28.962
All right, uh, there was this kid,
Billy Underwood.

40:29.177 --> 40:33.671
Beat me up every day
on the playground...

40:33.848 --> 40:35.179
...in fifth grade.

40:36.059 --> 40:41.771
Wedgies, especially.
Kid was, like, the Mozart of wedgies.

40:41.940 --> 40:46.605
And I swore that things would get better.

40:46.819 --> 40:48.730
And they did.

40:48.947 --> 40:50.483
I grew up...

40:50.657 --> 40:55.993
...and, heh, I got 300 employees...

40:56.162 --> 41:01.407
...and, heh, four homes and a wife...

41:02.794 --> 41:09.757
...who didn't care about any of it,
in the best possible way.

41:09.926 --> 41:14.420
And the punch line was the blackout.

41:14.597 --> 41:16.429
[SIGHS]

41:18.643 --> 41:20.930
When the world went back...

41:21.354 --> 41:25.188
...to being one giant school yard.

41:25.358 --> 41:29.898
And the Billy Underwoods
are in charge...

41:30.071 --> 41:34.690
...and I am weak and afraid.

41:37.578 --> 41:38.989
[WHIRRING]

41:43.918 --> 41:45.534
What is that?

41:46.838 --> 41:48.078
- Aaron.
- Oh, my God.

41:49.048 --> 41:50.083
[AARON CHUCKLES]

41:50.258 --> 41:52.545
[MARVIN GAYE'S "HEARD IT THROUGH THE
GRAPEVINE" PLAYS ON HEADPHONES]

41:53.261 --> 41:56.754
<i>Ooh, I bet you're wondering how I knew</i>

41:58.224 --> 42:01.558
<i>'Bout your plans to make me blue</i>

42:03.104 --> 42:04.720
It's music.

42:06.107 --> 42:08.098
It's Marvin Gaye, heh.

42:10.111 --> 42:13.900
<i>It took me by surprise, I must say</i>

42:14.782 --> 42:17.865
<i>When I found out yesterday</i>

42:18.036 --> 42:22.246
<i>Don't you know that
I heard it through the grapevine</i>

42:24.042 --> 42:25.532
[CHUCKLES]

42:26.836 --> 42:28.577
<i>Oh, I heard it through</i> the--

42:28.755 --> 42:29.790
[MUSIC STOPS]

42:35.678 --> 42:37.009
[SIGHS]

42:41.434 --> 42:42.640
How?

42:45.605 --> 42:47.346
I don't know.

43:30.233 --> 43:32.224
[English - US - SDH]
